    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1966 Pelham Bay Park was designated an NYC Landmark and in 1977 a National Historic Landmark.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.pelhambaypark.org/pelham-bay-park-timeline"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The neighborhood’s commercial heart is anchored by the Pelham Bay station on the 6 train, whose elevated tracks arch over Westchester Avenue.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.cityneighborhoods.nyc/pelham-bay"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The 1800s land originally purchased by Thomas Pell eventually yielded twenty‑thirty mansions that became summer retreats for the Bronx’s upper class.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.pelhambaypark.org/pelham-bay-park-timeline"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Pelham Bay’s library branch, part of the NYPL system, sits at 3060 Middletown Road and serves the community’s reading needs.",
